body:
The latest EAP is running with Java 17, so I had to make a few more changes than usual.

You need to have JAVA_HOME pointing to a Java 17 SDK to build the plugin for 2022.3.

We still use 2022.1 for testing. 2022.2 breaks a lot of tests.

The Gradle wrapper is now version 7.5, which can run on Java 17.

Two built-in plugins were renamed so I added those names to the `gradle.properties` file to be used in the build scripts.

cc @jacob314 @jwren @helin24
